Russia and the U.S. disagree on how to end the conflict in Syria - but both want the bloodshed to stop and the warring parties brought to the negotiating table, Vladimir Putin said today.

Russian President Mr Putin admitted after talks with U.S. President Barack Obama at the G8 summit in Northern Ireland that 'our positions do not fully coincide'.

He added: 'But we are united by the common intention to end the violence, to stop the number of victims increasing in Syria, to resolve the problems by peaceful means, including the Geneva talks.'

